<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-05T19:23:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-05T19:23:00-05:00" n="1065" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1065">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/173</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nogales</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-05T17:00:00-07:23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 5, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Decree number 56 dated May 18 signed by Calles given to press Saturday.
                            Provides that all mining properties in state which continue idle more
                            than 30 days from date of decree subject seizure and operation by State.
                            Will mail copy.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>